[4] Indonesia (West Sulawesi)
Date: Sat 7 Feb 2009
Source: Asia Pulse Data Source via COMTEX [edited]
<http://individual.com/story.php?story=96017890>


A dengue fever outbreak killed one person and infected 26 others in Mamuju
District, West Sulawesi Province, a local health official said.

The Mamuju health office declared the disease outbreak in the district as
an "extraordinary happening" [emergency] to anticipate the spreading of
dengue fever, Firmon, the Mamuju health service head, said [in Mamuju] on
Saturday [7 Feb 2009]. The 26 patients of dengue fever were currently being
hospitalized in Mamuju Public Hospital, he said.

The health office has distributed powder to kill the eggs of _Aedes
aegypti_ mosquitoes, which are usually laid on the surface of stagnant
water, and sprayed mosquito repellent, he said. The local health office
also set up 27 command posts in every community health center and hospitals
in the district to monitor the disease outbreak.

