[8] Sri Lanka
Date: Thu 5 Feb 2009
Source: Colombo Page [edited]
<http://www.colombopage.com/archive_09/February5184440RA.html>


Mosquitoborne dengue fever is spreading once again in the Colombo city
limit area with sharp increase in the number of patients, Sri Lanka health
officials today said [5 Feb 2009]. Dr Pradeep Kariyawasam, the chief
medical officer of the Colombo Municipal Council confirmed that 113 dengue
cases have been reported within Colombo city limits during last month
[January 2009]. According to the health sources, 2 children have already
died in the same period due to dengue fever.

Most dengue cases have been reported from Mattakkuliya, Modara, Hulftsdrop,
Borella, and Slave Island areas, Dr Kariyawasam said. Health officials
urged the people in Colombo city limits to destroy the mosquito
breeding-grounds to prevent the spreading of the disease.

