[9] Fiji
Date: Tue 3 Feb 2009
Source: Fijivillage.com [edited]
<http://www.fijivillage.com/?mod=archivedstory&id=0302099a43c836d8db743c256155be>


There has been an increase in the number of people suffering from [dengue]
and so far officials have confirmed 68 dengue fever cases. The General
Manager Community Health Central/Eastern, Dr Solo Qaranivalu says they have
received reports of an increase in viral infection cases from Rewa, Tailevu
and Naitasiri.

He says in Rewa, 9 people are currently suffering from dengue while in
Tailevu 3 dengue cases have been reported. In the Northern Division, 50
cases of dengue have been reported.

