[10] New Caledonia
Date: Fri 6 Feb 2009
Source: Radio Australia News [edited]
<http://www.radioaustralianews.net.au/stories/200902/2484612.htm?desktop>


In New Caledonia, about 500 new cases of dengue fever have been detected
this year [2009], prompting local authorities to label the outbreak an
epidemic. Health and social department authorities say they are worried by
the rapidly rising incidence of the disease, and say there have been 100
new cases in the past week alone [week of 1 Feb 2009]. Hotspots for the
epidemic include the capital, Noumea and its surrounding area, as well as
the southern part of the main island.

